According to our documentation on [Advanced Search - earliestUnreleasedVersion()|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Advanced+Searching#AdvancedSearching-earliestUnreleasedVersion]:

{quote}
Perform searches based on the earliest unreleased version (i.e. next version that is due to be released) of a specified project. See also unreleasedVersions.

Note that the "earliest" is determined by the ordering assigned to the versions, not by actual Version Due Dates.
{quote}

However, if we perform the following search:

{code:sql}
fixVersion = earliestUnreleasedVersion() 
{code}

If the versions of a given project don't have a release date set, the query won't retrieve any issues. 

I believe the query should retrieve the issues that are from the versions that have a release date set to a date bigger than the current date and also retrieve the issues that are from a version with no release date set.

