While viewing any issues, I think it would be useful to have a list of the current user's filters in which the currently viewed issue can be found. The idea here is to have quick access to all issues that fall within the current user's filters along side that issue.

Instead of running and caching a filter's results, this could be done by checking the current user's filters against the currently viewed issue. If a particular filter _would_ return the currently viewed issue in it's results, then have a link to that filter on the side.

